#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.62:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.62:0.2"
msgid "7. Pattakammavagga"
msgstr "7. Deeds of Substance"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: anaṇasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Ānaṇyasutta"
msgstr "62. Debtlessness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho "
"anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat "
"down to one side. The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, gahapati, sukhāni adhigamanīyāni gihinā kāmabhoginā kālena "
"kālaṃ samayena samayaṃ upādāya."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, these four kinds of happiness can be earned by a layperson who "
"enjoys sensual pleasures, depending on time and occasion."

msgctxt "an4.62:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: ānaṇyasukhaṃ → anaṇasukhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.62:2.3"
msgid "Atthisukhaṃ, bhogasukhaṃ, ānaṇyasukhaṃ, anavajjasukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The happiness of ownership, using wealth, debtlessness, and blamelessness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, gahapati, atthisukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the happiness of ownership?"

msgctxt "an4.62:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapati, kulaputtassa bhogā honti uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā "
"bāhābalaparicitā sedāvakkhittā dhammikā dhammaladdhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone from a good family owns legitimate wealth that he has "
"earned by his own efforts and initiative, built up with his own hands, "
"gathered by the sweat of the brow."

msgctxt "an4.62:3.3"
msgid ""
"So ‘bhogā me atthi uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatā bāhābalaparicitā sedāvakkhittā "
"dhammikā dhammaladdhā’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ."
msgstr "When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness."

msgctxt "an4.62:3.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, atthisukhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘the happiness of ownership’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, gahapati, bhogasukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the happiness of using wealth?"

msgctxt "an4.62:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapati, kulaputto uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi "
"sedāvakkhittehi dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi paribhuñjati puññāni ca karoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone from a good family uses his legitimate wealth, and makes "
"merit with it."

msgctxt "an4.62:4.3"
msgid ""
"So ‘uṭṭhānavīriyādhigatehi bhogehi bāhābalaparicitehi sedāvakkhittehi "
"dhammikehi dhammaladdhehi paribhuñjāmi puññāni ca karomī’ti adhigacchati "
"sukhaṃ, adhigacchati somanassaṃ."
msgstr "When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness."

msgctxt "an4.62:4.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, bhogasukhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘the happiness of using wealth’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, gahapati, ānaṇyasukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the happiness of debtlessness?"

#. VAR: kassaci kiñci dhāreti → kiñci vā deti (mr)
msgctxt "an4.62:5.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapati, kulaputto na kassaci kiñci dhāreti appaṃ vā bahuṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone from a good family owes no debt, large or small, to anyone."

msgctxt "an4.62:5.3"
msgid ""
"So ‘na kassaci kiñci dhāremi appaṃ vā bahuṃ vā’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, "
"adhigacchati somanassaṃ."
msgstr "When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness."

msgctxt "an4.62:5.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, ānaṇyasukhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘the happiness of debtlessness’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.70"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, gahapati, anavajjasukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the happiness of blamelessness?"

msgctxt "an4.62:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako anavajjena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, "
"anavajjena vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, anavajjena manokammena samannāgato "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple has blameless conduct by way of body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "an4.62:6.3"
msgid ""
"So ‘anavajjenamhi kāyakammena samannāgato, anavajjena vacīkammena "
"samannāgato, anavajjena manokammena samannāgato’ti adhigacchati sukhaṃ, "
"adhigacchati somanassaṃ."
msgstr "When he reflects on this, he’s filled with pleasure and happiness."

msgctxt "an4.62:6.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, gahapati, anavajjasukhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called ‘the happiness of blamelessness’."

msgctxt "an4.62:6.5"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, gahapati, cattāri sukhāni adhigamanīyāni gihinā kāmabhoginā "
"kālena kālaṃ samayena samayaṃ upādāyāti."
msgstr ""
"These four kinds of happiness can be earned by a layperson who enjoys "
"sensual pleasures, depending on time and occasion."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: Ānaṇyasukhaṃ ñatvāna → anaṇaṃ sukhaṃ ñatvāna (bj, s1-3) | anavajjasukhaṃ ñatvā (si)
msgctxt "an4.62:7.1"
msgid "Ānaṇyasukhaṃ ñatvāna,"
msgstr "Knowing the happiness of debtlessness,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: paraṃ → sare (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.62:7.2"
msgid "Atho atthisukhaṃ paraṃ;"
msgstr "and the extra happiness of possession,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: bhogasukhaṃ → bhogaṃ sukhaṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.62:7.3"
msgid "Bhuñjaṃ bhogasukhaṃ macco,"
msgstr "a mortal enjoying the happiness of using wealth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.62:7.4"
msgid "Tato paññā vipassati."
msgstr "then sees clearly with wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.62:8.1"
msgid "Vipassamāno jānāti,"
msgstr "Seeing clearly, a clever person knows"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.62:8.2"
msgid "ubho bhoge sumedhaso;"
msgstr "both kinds of happiness:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.62:8.3"
msgid "Anavajjasukhassetaṃ,"
msgstr "the other kind is not worth a sixteenth part"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.62:8.4"
msgid "kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasin”ti."
msgstr "of the happiness of blamelessness.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.62:8.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
